# RFQ Page — Corrected Visual Design Spec
## Environment-aware. Mechanism-tagged. Full reskin.

---

## 1 · Scope

**Full visual reskin of the RFQ grid and its chrome to match the approved renderings in `RFQ Prototype.html`.**
Not a behavior list. Not four targeted features. Every surface.

---

## 2 · Environment constraints (read before touching anything)

| Constraint | What it means for this spec |
|---|---|
| AG Grid v35 Theming API (`themeQuartz.withParams`) is active via the shared theme service | All color/typography must go into `withParams({})`. CSS variables (`--ag-*`) and `.ag-theme-alpine` overrides do nothing here. |
| `::ng-deep` still works for structural CSS | Heights, borders, seam shadow, cell-class tints — all fine as `::ng-deep` in `rfq.component.scss`. |
| Column `pinned` defaults are overridden by saved Views | Changing `pinned: 'left'` in a colDef silently does nothing for any user with a saved View. Fix: update the "Default" View record in the DB, and optionally call `gridApi.applyColumnState(…, { applyOrder: false })` on `firstDataRendered` for identity columns only. |
| `flex` and `sizeColumnsToFit()` conflict | Pick one per grid. Sub-grid uses `flex: 1` on Note column — do **not** also call `sizeColumnsToFit()`. |
| Group-band row is currently `headerClass` on leaf columns, NOT a `ColGroupDef` | True collapsible groups require migrating to `ColGroupDef` + `columnGroupShow`. The tinting spec below covers both the old (headerClass on leaf) and the new (headerGroupClass on group) approach. |
| Role-based column visibility | `admin` sees all 24 pricing columns. `sales`/`designer` see only "Price for Sales" leaves. The scenario cell tints and group bands must look correct in both role sets. |
| Backend detail-grid col IDs | Live colIds in the factory-quote sub-grid are `price`, `name`, `note` (not `quote_price`, `vendor_note`). Spec uses live IDs. |

---

## 3 · Type system decision

**App-wide (RFQ + Item Detail in sync):**

| Usage | Family | Weights used |
|---|---|---|
| UI text, labels, header text, cell text | **Hanken Grotesk** | 400, 500, 600, 700 |
| Price codes, numeric figures, monospaced values | **IBM Plex Mono** | 400, 500, 600 |

Load via Google Fonts or self-host. Apply to the grid via the `fontFamily` theme param (Hanken Grotesk stack). Apply IBM Plex Mono to price-code cells via a cell renderer or `::ng-deep .ag-cell.cell-price-code { font-family: … }`.

---

## 4 · themeQuartz.withParams() — complete parameter table

Replace (or extend) the existing `themePink` in `grid-themes.config.ts` with these values.
**Use these exact param names.**

```typescript
export const themePink = themeQuartz.withParams({
  // ── Accent + selection ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  accentColor:                     '#D81B60',          // checkboxes, focus rings, range selection border
  rangeSelectionBackgroundColor:   'rgba(216,27,96,0.07)',
  rangeSelectionBorderColor:       '#D81B60',

  // ── Background + row colours ──────────────────────────────────────────
  backgroundColor:                 '#ffffff',
  oddRowBackgroundColor:           '#fbfcfd',          // subtle zebra (was none)
  rowHoverColor:                   '#fff5f8',          // faint pink hover
  selectedRowBackgroundColor:      '#fff5f8',          // matches hover; pink tint for selected row

  // ── Foreground / text ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  foregroundColor:                 '#1a202e',          // primary ink
  textColor:                       '#475569',          // secondary ink for cells

  // ── Borders ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  borderColor:                     '#e7e9ee',
  wrapperBorder:                   { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },
  wrapperBorderRadius:             8,
  borderRadius:                    0,                  // no cell-level rounding
  rowBorder:                       { color: '#eef1f5', width: 1 },  // hairline row divider
  columnBorder:                    { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },
  headerColumnBorder:              { color: '#e7e9ee', width: 1 },

  // ── Header ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  headerBackgroundColor:           '#f7f9fc',
  headerTextColor:                 '#475569',
  headerFontWeight:                600,
  headerFontSize:                  11,                 // pt; rendered uppercase via ::ng-deep below

  // ── Typography ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  fontFamily:
    '"Hanken Grotesk", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif',
  fontSize:                        13,                 // comfortable default; density overrides via setGridOption

  // ── Spacing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  spacing:                         8,
  cellHorizontalPadding:           10,
  rowVerticalPaddingScale:         1,
});
```

> **Density switching** (`rowHeight`) is NOT a theme param; it goes through
> `this.gridApi.setGridOption('rowHeight', n)` + `this.gridApi.resetRowHeights()`.
> See §8 Toolbar for the density-toggle spec.

---

## 5 · Per-surface spec

Each item is tagged:
- **[theme param]** — value in `withParams({})` above, nothing else needed
- **[::ng-deep CSS]** — structural override in `rfq.component.scss`
- **[cell renderer]** — requires a custom Angular `ICellRendererAngularComp`
- **[colDef]** — property on the column definition in `rfq.grid.config.ts`
- **[component SCSS]** — styles in the component's own SCSS file

---

### 5a · 3-row header (group band · column header · floating filter)

The header has three stacked rows. Current heights: all 60px + filter 50px = 170px total.
Target: group band 36px + column header 48px + floating filter 44px = **128px total**.

```scss
// rfq.component.scss  — replaces the existing .ag-header-row block

// Row 1: scenario group band
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row:first-child {
  height: 36px !important;
}

// Row 2: column headers (allows up to 2 lines of text)
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row:nth-child(2) {
  height: 48px !important;
}

// Row 3: floating filters
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-row-floating-filter {
  height: 44px !important;
}

// Header text: uppercase + letter-spacing (font color/weight from theme param)
::ng-deep .grid-wrapper .ag-header-cell-text {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  white-space: normal !important;
  line-height: 1.2;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2 !important;   // was 3; target shows 2 lines max
  max-height: 2.4em !important;
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** for heights + text-transform.

#### Group-band row — per-family tints

Two families, two color systems. Replaces the current 8-color rainbow.

| Family | Band background | Band text / icon |
|---|---|---|
| **General** (Gen · FOB / POE / WHSE / MDDP) | `#dbe7fb` | `#2456b8` |
| **Licensed** (Lic · FOB / POE / WHSE / MDDP) | `#e9ddf7` | `#7a3bb8` |

When `ColGroupDef` is used (collapsible groups), set `headerGroupClass` on each group:
```typescript
// rfq.grid.config.ts — on each ColGroupDef
{ headerGroupClass: 'group-band-gen', … }  // General families
{ headerGroupClass: 'group-band-lic', … }  // Licensed families
```

CSS:
```scss
// rfq.component.scss — replaces the 8 group-header-* rules

// Group band cells (ColGroupDef header row)
::ng-deep .ag-header-group-cell.group-band-gen {
  background-color: #dbe7fb !important;
  color: #2456b8 !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}
::ng-deep .ag-header-group-cell.group-band-lic {
  background-color: #e9ddf7 !important;
  color: #7a3bb8 !important;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

// If still using headerClass on leaf columns (old approach, pre-ColGroupDef migration):
::ng-deep .ag-header-cell[class*="group-header-gen"] {
  background-color: #eaf1fd !important;
  .ag-header-cell-text, .ag-header-cell-label { color: #2456b8 !important; }
}
::ng-deep .ag-header-cell[class*="group-header-lic"] {
  background-color: #f3ecfb !important;
  .ag-header-cell-text, .ag-header-cell-label { color: #7a3bb8 !important; }
}
```
**[::ng-deep CSS]** + **[colDef `headerGroupClass`]**.

> The current 8-color system (blue/purple/green/orange/pink/teal/amber/lavender) is replaced
> by this 2-family system. Update the 8 `group-header-*` rules in the existing SCSS.

---

### 5b · Data rows

| Property | Value | Mechanism |
|---|---|---|
| Row background | `#ffffff` | [theme param] `backgroundColor` |
| Odd-row zebra | `#fbfcfd` | [theme param] `oddRowBackgroundColor` |
| Row hover | `#fff5f8` | [theme param] `rowHoverColor` |
| Selected row | `#fff5f8` | [theme param] `selectedRowBackgroundColor` |
| Row border (horizontal) | `1px solid #eef1f5` | [theme param] `rowBorder` |
| Cell border (vertical) | `1px solid #e7e9ee` | [theme param] `columnBorder` |
